Java Restful Services
Fee: 5k
duration: 3 months to 3 months, 15 days
timings: 8:05 am - 9:05 am [Monday - Saturday] [no sunday]
Live classroom notes: will be provided on weekly basis to the students
No recordings, no subscription, no bell icon, No youtube. The students are not permitted to record the classes, if found anyone recording the admission will be cancelled without fee refund. 

pre-requisite:
1. jdk8 
2. servlet api [no jsp required]
3. basic knowledge on distributed technology and distributed webapplication development
4. packaging and deploying the applications on Servlet container
5. [optional]: spring framework #mvc module = last 10/15 sessions while explaining developing restful services using spring framework

Part#1:
course content
1. Introduction to Distributed Technology, why do we need it
2. What are Restful Services, evolution of them?
3. Restful Service Principles
4. Basics of Http protocol
5. Architecture of Restful Services
6. Programming Restful Services
	- Path Parameter
	- Method Designators
	- Bootstrapping 
	- query parameters
	- Interfaces & Abstract classes
	- SubResources
	- SubResource locators
7. Jaxrs Injection
	- Template Parameters
	- Query Parameters
	- Header Parameters
	- Cookie Parameters
	- Matrix Parameters
	- PathSegment
	- UriInfo
	- HttpHeaders
	- Automatic Parameter Converters
	- Custom Type Converters
	- Bean Parameter
	
8. Json (javax.json api)
	- Json Parsing
	- Json Binding
	- Json Streaming
	
9. Content Handlers
	- Built-in support for Contents Handlers
	- Custom Content Handlers (MessageBodyReaders/MessageBodyWriters)
	- Provider
	
10. working with client api	
11. Exception Handling in Restful Services
12. Server Responses
13. Caching
14. Asynchronous Programming in Restful Services
15. Security
		1. Basic Authentication
		2. OAuth2 (Spring boot/Spring cloud)
16. Swagger & Integrating Restful Services with Swagger
